    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.n1a.1.1"/>
                <note type="curatorial">1</note>
                <fw type="curatorial"></fw>
                
                <opener>

                    <dateline> 
                        June 28, 1911
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>
                            Barrytown N.Y.
                        </addrLine>
                    </address>
                    
                    <salute>My dear Mr. Neihardt/</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I have just re read your review of my "Learning and other essays" in the Sunday Times. I knew from your letter that the review be favorable; but I was not prepared for such a blast, nor have I ever had anything like it. By some likeness of inner history the essays mean to you what I meant them to say. But what a wonderful coincidence that this man should be chosen to review the volume! And how much more am I getting than any man has a right to expect in the way ^of what he thinks is understanding of his work. Thank you - or rather thank God for the conjunction</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Your friend</salute>
                    
                    <signed>John Jay Chapman</signed>

                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
